  "prompt": "When sperm sits inside the vagina does it have a smelly odor to it?",
  "response": "Semen itself has a characteristic odor that some people might describe as mildly earthy or musky, but it can vary based on numerous factors, such as diet, hydration, and overall health. When sperm is inside the vagina, it typically does not develop a strong or foul smell on its own. However, odors can change or develop due to the natural flora and bacteria present in the vagina, as well as potential infections or other factors.\n\nIf someone notices a strong or unpleasant odor, it might be worth consulting a healthcare professional, as it could be a sign of an infection or other medical issue.",
